-- Indian Hotels to Run Properties in Beijing, Hainan, Shanghai, Xinhua Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-09-24T18:45:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/indian-hotels-to-run-properties-in-beijing-hainan-shanghai-xinhua-says.html
Indian Hotels Co . plans to set up
at least three hotels in China soon, Xinhua News Agency
reported, citing Chief Executive Officer  Raymond Bickson , who
spoke in Colombo, Sri Lanka.  The company, called Taj Hotels Resorts & Palaces, has
signed a contract to manage the Temple of Heaven Hotel in
Beijing and the Xiangshuiwan hotel in Hainan province, and plans
to set up a hotel in Shanghai, Xinhua said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  